article.headline: UAB 86, South Florida 47
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Mo Finley scored 17 points and Demario Eddins added 13 to lead UAB to a 86-47 rout of South Florida. Eddins, making his first start in three weeks, sparked an 18-0 first-half run that put UAB (10-5, 3-1 Conference USA) in charge. Donell Taylor scored 11 points and made two fast-break layups in UAB's early spurt. UAB used sharp ball handling and passing to get good shots. The Blazers finished with 26 assists and only six turnovers while shooting 49 percent from the field. Bradley Moseley scored 18 points to lead South Florida (6-8, 0-3). The Bulls got 14 points and nine rebounds from Terrence Leather. Eddins hit a layup and completed a 3-pointer to stake UAB to an early 8-6 lead. And inside basket by Gabe Kennedy started the 18-0 run that put the Blazers on top 26-6. Derrick Broom hit a pair of 3-pointers during the run. UAB built a 24 point lead in the first half, but South Florida went on a 13-0 run driven by Sam Barber's back-to-back 3-pointers. The Bulls cut the lead to 36-24 at halftime, but UAB started the second half with an 11-2 run to blow the game open. Finley scored 14 points in the second half, hitting four 3-pointers.
